original: Axen, Axel Bertil, ingenjör, Jönköping, f. 25/10/18 i Söderhamn av Axel Axén o. Elna KarliS’Son. G. 45 m. Ingrid Lagergren. — Tekn. gymn. i Örebro 42. Anst. v. SAAB i Linköping 42, v. Statens Vattenfalls verk i Motala 43-44, besiiktningsingenjör v. Mellersta o. Norra Sv :es Ångpanne-fören. ised. 44. Hobbies : istudier o. friluftsliv. *Axén, Oskar Helmer, komminister. Torsås, f. 26/9/07 i Hakarp, Jönköp. 1., av Oiskar A. o. Hulda Qvick. G. 38 m. Ulla Törnquist. Barn: Kjell f. 39. — Stud:ex. i Jönköp. 28, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 30, teol. kand. samt prakt. teol. prov 34, prästv. f. Växjö stift 35. Varit past:adj. i Rogberga, Alseda o. Berga samt v. kommin. i Almesåkra, kommin. i Bondstorp 37, i Torsås sed. 45.
translated:
Axen, Axel Bertil, engineer, Jönköping, born 25/10/18 in Söderhamn to Axel Axén and Elna KarliS’Son. Married to Ingrid Lagergren for 45 years. Attended Technical High School in Örebro in 1942. Employed by SAAB in Linköping in 1942, worked for the State Power Company in Motala from 1943-44, and became an inspection engineer with the Middle and Northern Swedish Steam Boiler Association in 1944. Hobbies included ice studies and outdoor activities. 

Axén, Oskar Helmer, pastor in Torsås, born 26/9/07 in Hakarp, Jönköping County, son of Oiskar A. and Hulda Qvick. Married to Ulla Törnquist for 38 years, and has a son named Kjell born in 1939. Obtained a high school diploma in Jönköping in 1928, studied theology and philosophy at Lund University from 1928-1930, passed the practical theology exam in 1934, and was ordained as a priest for the Växjö diocese in 1935. Has served as a pastor's assistant in Rogberga, Alseda, and Berga, as a vicar in Almesåkra from 1937 and in Bondstorp from 1937, and has been a pastor in Torsås since 1945.
